    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-21T17:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-21T17:30:00-05:00" n="871"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.74/951: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-21T18:30:00-04:00"
                            >January 21, 1943—6:30 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 27—noon.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–122. Reference Department’s airgram no. 435 of January 9, 3:05 p.m. West Coast
                    Telegraph Company was instructed only on or about January 15 by Cables and
                    Wireless that it was not to accept for transmission to the Axis and Axis
                    controlled countries including Vichy.</p>
                <p>The telecommunications companies were instructed yesterday by the Chilean
                    Government (reference my telegram no. 136, January 21, 6 p.m.<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d871fn43">Not printed.</note>) not to accept any messages for
                    Germany, Italy and Japan and countries controlled by them. Consequently, all the
                    companies are now operating on the same terms.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
